==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: avant-garde
<hw>a*vant`-garde"</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*v⟦aum⟧nt"-g⟦aum⟧rd`)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>avant</ets> before + E. <ets>guard</ets>, F.
<ets>avant-garde</ets>. See <er>Avaunt</er>.]</ety> <def>The most
advanced group of people in any field of endeavor, especially in
literary and artistic work, usually characterized by new ideas and
experimental techniques.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>avant-garde</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: avant-garde
<hw>a*vant`-garde"</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*v⟦aum⟧nt"-g⟦aum⟧rd`)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of, pertaining to, or belonging to the
avant-garde.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by the use of experimental techniques;
modern; daring; radical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>avant-guard</ent>⟦br⟧
